#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/examples/00-load/create_sphere.rst:1093
msgid "Structured quadrilateral mesh of Sphere"
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/examples/00-load/create_sphere.rst:1094
msgid ""
"The structure of the mesh can be important. Instead of a triangulated mesh, "
"it can be useful to have a structured mesh that has an i-j-k ordering that "
"allows for simplified cell connectivity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/examples/00-load/create_sphere.rst:1099
msgid ""
"The points are generated as a regular grid in spherical coordinates using "
":func:`pyvista.spherical_to_cartesian`. Here, we will used the convention "
"that ``theta`` is the azimuthal angle, similar to longitude on the globe.  "
"``phi`` is the polar angle, similar to latitude on the globe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/examples/00-load/create_sphere.rst:1129
msgid ""
"The mesh has :attr:`~pyvista.CellType.QUAD` cells. The cells that look "
"triangular at the poles are actually degenerate quadrilaterals, i.e. two "
"points are coincident at the pole, as will be shown later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../pyvista/doc/source/examples/00-load/create_sphere.rst:1176
msgid "The mesh is of type :class:`pyvista.StructuredGrid`."
msgstr ""

